<subSubSection id="C31F6781D714FFDE81D7FE1989365C29" pageId="2" pageNumber="29" type="description">
<paragraph id="8BBA340AD714FFDE81D7FE1989025D08" blockId="2.[166,1225,500,847]" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">
C o l o r a t i o n. F e m a l e. Generally body colour as in 
<taxonomicName id="4C054F89D714FFDE826AFE188E5F5D69" baseAuthorityName="Linnaeus" baseAuthorityYear="1758" box="[870,1093,500,526]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Rhyssa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="persuasoria">
<emphasis id="B971E818D714FFDE826AFE188E5F5D69" box="[870,1093,500,526]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">Rhyssa persuasoria</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, but white marks also on mesoscutum. Legs generally red, all coxae and hind femora varying from red to brown, sometimes with yellow spots, hind tibiae and tarsi fuscous. Propodeum and metasoma entirely smooth and polished. OTI 8.0–9.0
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBA340AD714FFDE81D7FD998BF75DC8" blockId="2.[166,1225,500,847]" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">M a l e. Body colour as in female, but metasoma usually entirely black, with at most two white spots on tergite I.</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBA340AD714FFDE81D7FD598AEA5C68" blockId="2.[166,1225,500,847]" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">
R e m a r k. From other species of the genus, 
<taxonomicName id="4C054F89D714FFDE83F5FD59896E5DA9" baseAuthorityName="Schellenberg" baseAuthorityYear="1802" box="[761,884,693,718]" class="Insecta" family="Ichneumonidae" genus="Megarhyssa" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="29" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="rixator">
<emphasis id="B971E818D714FFDE83F5FD59896E5DA9" box="[761,884,693,718]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">M. rixator</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
differs in the black clypeus, mesosoma and metasoma and in the structure of the male parameres (see 
<bibRefCitation id="EF9449FBD714FFDE8535FD398AF95C68" author="Horstmann, K." pageId="2" pageNumber="29" pagination="337 - 352" refId="ref4964" refString="Horstmann, K. Die europaishen Arten von Megarhyssa Ashmead, 1900 (Hymenoptera, Ichneumonidae) // Entomofauna. - 1998. - 19, N 22. - S. 337 - 352." type="book chapter" year="1998">Horstmann, 1998</bibRefCitation>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BBA340AD714FFDE81D7FCF989365C29" blockId="2.[166,1225,500,847]" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">
D i s t r i b u t i o n. Palaearctic: 
<collectingCountry id="F312749AD714FFDE834BFCF888BB5C49" box="[583,673,788,814]" name="Austria" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">Austria</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F312749AD714FFDE83BDFCF8896A5C49" box="[689,880,788,814]" name="Czech Republic" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">Czech Republic</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F312749AD714FFDE828CFCF989EB5C48" box="[896,1009,789,815]" name="Germany" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">Germany</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F312749AD714FFDE850EFCF88E425C49" box="[1026,1112,788,814]" name="Poland" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">Poland</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F312749AD714FFDE8564FCF88AC65C29" name="Switzerland" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">Switzerland</collectingCountry>
, 
<collectingCountry id="F312749AD714FFDE81EBFCD88B295C29" box="[231,307,820,846]" name="Russia" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">Russia</collectingCountry>
(Chita, 
<collectingRegion id="49C1FAE8D714FFDE809FFCD88BD35C29" box="[403,457,820,846]" country="Russia" name="Tula" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">Tula</collectingRegion>
and 
<collectingRegion id="49C1FAE8D714FFDE830EFCD888755C29" box="[514,623,820,846]" country="Russia" name="Yaroslavl'" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">Yaroslavl</collectingRegion>
Regs); 
<collectingCountry id="F312749AD714FFDE83C9FCD889325C29" box="[709,808,820,846]" name="Ukraine" pageId="2" pageNumber="29">Ukraine</collectingCountry>
.
</paragraph>
